{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Calls repeat_rows and clip_input functions on the input.\n\n    Args:\n    input: A list of lists containing integers.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of lists containing integers, with each row repeated six times vertically and values clipped between the minimum and maximum values of input.\n    \"\"\"\n    output = repeat_rows(input)\n    output = clip_input(output, input)\n    return output\ndef repeat_rows(input: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Repeats the rows of the input six times vertically.\n\n    Args:\n    input: A list of lists containing integers.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of lists containing integers, with each row repeated six times vertically.\n    \"\"\"\n    clipped_input = input[3:6]\n    repeated_input = [clipped_input] * 6\n    return np.array(repeated_input).reshape(-1, len(input[0])).tolist()\ndef clip_input(input1: List[List[int]], input2: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Clips the values of input1 between the minimum and maximum values of input2.\n\n    Args:\n    input1: A list of lists containing integers.\n    input2: A list of lists containing integers.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of lists containing integers, with values clipped between the minimum and maximum values of input2.\n    \"\"\"\n    return np.clip(input1, a_min=None, a_max=np.array(input2).shape)", "user_code": "", "gpt_code": "def main(input: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Calls repeat_rows and clip_input functions on the input.\n\n    Args:\n    input: A list of lists containing integers.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of lists containing integers, with each row repeated six times vertically and values clipped between the minimum and maximum values of input.\n    \"\"\"\n    output = repeat_rows(input)\n    output = clip_input(output, input)\n    return output\ndef repeat_rows(input: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int